Imagine if you could cycle or run from Stratford to Ealing on closed roads every Sunday? Meet Ciclopaseo, Quito. Every South American city worth it's salt has a ciclova/paseo from Bogota to Medellin to Santiago to Quito.
This time on bike con Guillermo. Another goodbye after an amazing 3 and a half days of exploring Quito.

Little bit of a hike up and down to crater before breakfast. Very quiet and I'm almost the only gringo in the village. Very sad that Ecuador's tourism industry has sunk since Covid. This is one of most stunning sites in South America.

Just a stroll around an extinct caldera volcano. I've been wanting to do this walk since my first trip to South America 10 years ago. Didn't come across a single other hiker  Paid an excessive $3 for a mate de coca half way round but don't blame the vender who explained how people are much poorer since tourist numbers declined.
Not too much here but a gateway to Cotapaxi and Quilatoa para los gringos. Fly to Chile tonight via Peru.
